.th ABS VI "October 1979"
.sh NAME
abs \*- takes absolute value of a picture file
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd abs
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Abs
reads a picture file with GAP style header from standard input,
takes the absolute value of every pixel, and writes the resulting
picture file to standard output. May be used as a filter.
.sh FILES
.in +10
.ti -10
abs.c - C source code
.ti -10
unop.t - driver program for unary picture operators in general
.ti -10
defns.t - useful definitions
.i0
.sh DIAGNOSTICS
.in +10
.ti -10
"Input picture not a byte per pixel file!"
.br
- header byte count not one
.ti -10
"Premature end of input!"
.br
- picture smaller than expected from
size given in header
.ti -10
"Excess input data remaining!"
.br
- picture bigger than expected from size in header
.i0
.sh AUTHOR
Les Kitchen
.sh "SEE ALSO"
unop(VII)
.sh BUGS
Works only for 1 byte per pixel files.
.br
Read error will also cause "Premature end of input!" message.
